{
  "text": "The adverse drug reaction is monitored by the tracer drugs like Pheniramine maleate injection and by checking indications for which they were prescribed, during hospital rounds. If any adverse drug reaction occurs it is reported on an ADR reporting form. All details regarding the suspected drug e.g. brand and generic name, doses, route of administration should be documented. [CITATION_1] The ADR should be described according to the signs and categorized according to the severity.",
